						<summary>

						<p>This is partly damaged. It records a gift of 90 sheep left in charge of a local shepherd by••••••••• <hi rend="bold">Kalaṅgāśuḍar daughter of Dēvanār of Āyirattaḷi</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva at Tiruchchōṟṟuttuṟṟi. It is possible that this <hi rend="bold">Dēvaṉār</hi> is the same as the chief of that name mentioned in a Mēlappaḻuvūr inscription of Rajakēsarivarman (No. 153 of S.I.I. Vol. XIII) as the father of the donor <hi rend="bold">Nakkaṟ Akkāranaṅgaiyār.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
